
[1]liability

   LIABIL'ITY, n.

   1. The state of being bound or obliged in law or justice;
   responsibility. The officer wishes to discharge himself from his
   liability.

   2. Exposedness; tendency; a state of being subject; as the liableness
   of a man to contract disease in an infected room; a liability to
   accidents.
